name: Regex-Ace
tagline: Regex Ace is a regular expression tester for the windows and linux desktops.
body:
### Regex-Ace.
Regex-Ace is an on the fly regular expression tester for multiple programming languages on the desktop.
As of 1.0 beta only Python support is implemented, but support Ruby and Perl is planned for subsequent versio

### Authors and Contributors
You can @mention a GitHub username to generate a link to their profile. The resulting `<a>` element will link to the contributor's GitHub Profile. For example: In 2007, Chris Wanstrath (@defunkt), PJ Hyett (@pjhyett), and Tom Preston-Werner (@mojombo) founded GitHub.
